<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">Global Consumer &amp; Small Business Banking Product Leader Development Program</h1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>

<p class="bac">
	Global Consumer and Small Business Banking (GCSBB) serves more than 59 million consumers and mass-market small business relationships across America through a distribution network of 6,100 banking centers, 18,500 ATMs, and the nation’s leading online bill pay and mobile banking services, as well as through a world class sales forces and call centers.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
	The Global Consumer &amp; Small Business Banking Product Leader Development Program develops future senior leaders while engaging them in challenging projects critical to the future of Bank of America. Recent MBA/Masters-level graduates experience two to three rotational assignments (6-8 months each) over 18-24 months.
</p>
<p class="bac">Rotational opportunities include:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Business Operations Management</li>
	<li>Marketing</li>
	<li>Product  Management</li>
	<li>Process Design</li>
	<li>Distribution Strategy</li>
</ul>


<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">
	Ideal candidate will exhibit a strong drive for results; succeed in a fast-paced, empowered, and collaborative environment; enjoy teamwork and partnering with others; possess excellent organizational and analytical skills; understand technology and business requirements.  The ability to learn the organizational structure and the formal/informal workings of the organization and to convey a strong sense of customer and associate satisfaction to drive shareholder value is required.  Additional requirements include:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>MBA or Master’s graduate from an accredited business school or University.</li>
	<li>Spring/Summer 2009 graduation date.</li>
	<li>3–6 years pre-M.B.A. work experience with a demonstrated record of achievement.</li>
	<li>Relevant work history that reflects experience in supervising others, delegating tasks and resolving conflicts.</li>
	<li>Must have eligibility to work in US.</li>
	<li>Geographic mobility</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Expertise and/or experience in at least 3 of the following:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Familiarity with database marketing and segmentation principles</li>
	<li>Experience in execution/production for end to end marketing campaign management processes.</li>
	<li>Previous financial services or retail experience</li>
	<li>Strong statistical background (Black Belt certified or an experienced Statistician in the deep drilling of data sets) and ability to use statistical methodology and tools (e.g., SPSS and SAS) to conduct and report on market research</li>
	<li>3+ years of pricing, valuation, and/or risk management experience</li>
	<li>Experience with SQL, Access and database management</li>
	<li>Proficiency in a second foreign language (e.g., Spanish, Korean, etc.)</li>
</ul>

<p class="bac">
Personal characteristics
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ability to successfully navigate in a complex environment</li>
	<li>Strong leadership potential</li>
	<li>Results oriented, proven high level of performance</li>
	<li>Ability to manage tight deadlines, organize, and prioritize work independently</li>
	<li>Flexibility in exploring a variety of business areas</li>
</ul>


<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training</h2>
<p class="bac">
	Associates will participate in a formal Education and Orientation program to learn more about Bank of America business, culture and values, as well as to network with Executives and other college hires.  Additionally, associates will participate in various networking and learning opportunities throughout the duration of the program. LDP participants will attend an exclusive session designed to build critical leadership skills using assessments, experiential learning and senior leader exposure.
</p>

